<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="848" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d848">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/308C.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Ambassador of the French
                                    Republic</gloss>.</hi><note n="1" xml:id="d848fn1">Mutatis
                                mutandis to the Ambassador of Great Britain and the German
                                Ambassador.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-13">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to enclose
                            herewith for your information a copy of the loan agreement<note n="2" xml:id="d848fn2">Not printed.</note> between the Republic of Liberia
                            and the bankers, for the refunding of the Republic’s bonded debt, which
                            was signed on the 7th instant. A duplicate original of this loan
                            agreement will be transmitted to the French Government through the
                            diplomatic representative of Liberia to the Republic of France.</p>
                        <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>